          "type": "plan",
          "text": "# Plan: Add AWS Full Jitter to Retry Backoff\n\n## Context\n\nIssue #62: Both retry paths use pure exponential backoff with zero jitter. Multiple clients retrying against the same node synchronize their retries, creating thundering-herd bursts. The fix is to apply **AWS Full Jitter**: `sleep = random_between(0, min(cap, base * 2^attempt))`, which spreads retries uniformly across the backoff window.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. `crates/reme-outbox/Cargo.toml` — Add `rand` dependency\n- Add `rand = { workspace = true }` to `[dependencies]`\n\n### 2. `crates/reme-outbox/src/config.rs:163` — `TransportRetryPolicy::delay_for_attempt()`\n- Add `use rand::Rng;` at top of file\n- Change the method to apply full jitter: instead of returning the deterministic backoff delay, return `random_between(0, capped_delay)`:\n```rust\npub fn delay_for_attempt(&self, attempt: u32) -> Duration {\n    if attempt == 0 {\n        return Duration::ZERO;\n    }\n    let multiplier = self.backoff_multiplier.powi(attempt.saturating_sub(1) as i32);\n    let delay_ms = self.initial_delay.as_millis() as f32 * multiplier;\n    let capped = delay_ms.min(self.max_delay.as_millis() as f32);\n    let jittered = rand::rng().random_range(0.0..=capped);\n    Duration::from_millis(jittered as u64)\n}\n```\n\n### 3. `crates/reme-transport/src/delivery.rs:662` — `TieredDeliveryConfig::calculate_retry_delay()`\n- Add `use rand::Rng;` at top of file\n- Apply the same full jitter pattern:\n```rust\npub fn calculate_retry_delay(&self, attempt: u32) -> Duration {\n    let delay = self.urgent_initial_delay.as_secs_f32()\n        * self.urgent_backoff_multiplier.powi(attempt as i32);\n    let capped = delay.min(self.urgent_max_delay.as_secs_f32());\n    let jittered = rand::rng().random_range(0.0..=capped);\n    Duration::from_secs_f32(jittered)\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Update tests in both files\nSince jitter makes results non-deterministic, tests must change from exact equality to range checks:\n- `delay_for_attempt(n)` should return a value in `0..=deterministic_cap`\n- `calculate_retry_delay(n)` should return a value in `0..=deterministic_cap`\n\n**Outbox tests** (`config.rs:222-248`):\n- `test_retry_policy_delay`: Assert each delay is `<= expected_deterministic_value`  and `>= Duration::ZERO`\n- `test_retry_policy_max_delay`: Assert delay `<= max_delay` (30s)\n- Keep `attempt == 0` returning exactly `Duration::ZERO`\n\n**Transport tests** (`delivery.rs:797-817`):\n- `test_retry_delay_calculation`: Assert each delay is `<= expected_cap` and `>= Duration::ZERO`\n\n## Files to modify\n1. `crates/reme-outbox/Cargo.toml`\n2. `crates/reme-outbox/src/config.rs`\n3. `crates/reme-transport/src/delivery.rs`\n\n## Verification\n```bash\ncargo test -p reme-outbox\ncargo test -p reme-transport\ncargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings\ncargo fmt --all -- --check\n```\n",
